name: The Fairly OddParents
overview: The zany, fast-paced adventures of a 10-year-old boy and his fairy godparents, who inadvertently create havoc as they grant wishes for their pint-sized charge.

episodes.name: The Big Problem
episodes.overview: Tired of being a kid, Timmy wishes he could be older in order to go adult things, but his wish backfires when "Da Rules" states that now that he is an adult, Cosmo and Wanda can't grant him any wishes or turn him back into a kid until he is a kid or acts like a kid.

episodes.name: Power Mad
episodes.overview: After wishing for a challenging virtual reality game, Timmy goes to the bathroom and leaves it unattended, and Chester and AJ decide to play. Realizing what has happened, Timmy must go into the game and play to save them.

episodes.name: Spaced Out
episodes.overview: While watching Crash Nebula, Timmy wishes for an alien to play with. So, Cosmo and Wanda take a real alien prince - Mark. His parents are furious and travel to Earth to blow it up.  In the meantime, Mark has fallen in love with Vicky, and Timmy can't wish him away because GodParents can't interfere with true love. Timmy goes to Mark's parents and asks them to convince their son to forget about Vicky, but Timmy must first pass their toughest tests. Will he be able to fix this mess and save the Earth from destruction?

episodes.name: TransParents
episodes.overview: After Timmy brings an extinct dinosaur to school, his crazy teacher suspects that he has Fairy GodParents, so he tells Timmy he wants to have a conference with his "parents." Since he has aspirations of "a new world order," he thinks that if he catches fairies, he can harness their power and rule the Earth. Timmy knows he can't explain to his real parents how he managed to come across an extinct dinosaur, so Cosmo and Wanda pose as his parents.

episodes.name: A Wish Too Far
episodes.overview: Timmy has a giant crush on Trixie Tang, the most popular girl in school, but she doesn't even know he exists. In order to get Trixie to notice him, Timmy wishes for a long list of superficial things to make him popular.

episodes.name: Tiny Timmy
episodes.overview: Cosmo and Wanda shrink Timmy so he can complete his assignment on the microscopic universe but problems ensue when Cosmo and Wanda, who have also shrunk themselves, get eaten by Vicky. Timmy must now go inside Vicky to save his godparents but stirs up a lot of trouble in the process. To make matters worse, Vicky plans on tearing apart the house and blaming it all on Timmy to his parents.

episodes.name: Father Time!
episodes.overview: When Timmy breaks his dad's sentimental, grade school trophy and gets punished, he wishes himself back in time to stop his dad (as a kid) from ever winning the dumb thing in the first place.

episodes.name: Apartnership
episodes.overview: After Wanda gets mad at Cosmo on their umpteenth anniversary, Cosmo visits Fairy World. There, his mom, who has always hated Wanda, announces that she has found him two new girlfriends, Twinkle and Star. In order to get Cosmo back, Wanda must compete against Twinkle and Star in a game show hosted by Cupid, but Cosmo's mom will do anything to ensure that he doesn't go home with Wanda.

episodes.name: Chin Up
episodes.overview: Timmy meets his favorite superhero, The Crimson Chin, but the discovery that he is fictional sends the hero into a deep depression. Timmy must now reverse this situation, and as a result, he gains the superhero alter-ego of Cleft the Boy Chin Wonder.

episodes.name: Dog's Day Afternoon
episodes.overview: Timmy switches lives with Vicky's dog, but swiftly discovers that the dog actually has it just as badly as he does.

guest_stars.character: Vet / Teacher / Chet / Barry / TV Wrestler (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: Dream Goat
episodes.overview: When Timmy feels sorry for the town's caged, prize goat, Chompy, and wishes he could be free, the goat disappears and Vicky gets blamed for goat-napping.

episodes.name: The Same Game
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for everyone in the world to be the same when an evil dentist won't give him his ball back. Problems inevitably ensue, and Timmy can't wish things back to normal as Cosmo and Wanda aren't able figure out who he is.

episodes.name: Boys in the Band
episodes.overview: Vicky has kidnapped teen singing sensation Chip Skylark. A stadium full of screaming girls (and Mrs. Turner) are going to tear the town apart if he doesn't perform for them.

episodes.name: Hex Games
episodes.overview: Timmy tries to beat Vicky at a skateboarding contest so he can become queen (eh, king) of the skate park.

episodes.name: Boy Toy
episodes.overview: Hoping for one last adventure with his Crimson Chin action figure, Timmy wishes to be doll-sized.

episodes.name: Inspection Detection
episodes.overview: Thanks to all the stuff he's gotten from his fairies, Timmy's parents suspect that he's a shoplifter. On the same day, Cosmo and Wanda have an inspection day with Jorgen Von Strangle. Timmy must prove his innocence while his godparents prove their competence or they'll never see each other again.

episodes.name: Action Packed
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that his entire life was like an action movie,  but things quickly turn to chaos when all of his loved ones are put in danger.

episodes.name: Smarty Pants
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that he knew everything in the world so he can beat A-student A.J. at the Brain-A-Thon.

episodes.name: Timvisible
episodes.overview: Timmy's shot at the perfect attendance award is threatened by bully Francis. Timmy wishes to become invisible, but soon, everyone believes the school is haunted. That is, except Crocker, who knows that catching Timmy will be all the evidence he needs to prove the existence of Fairies.

episodes.name: That Old Black Magic
episodes.overview: Timmy goes to an amusement park in Friday the 13th and he figures that something is destroying the park, until Cosmo and Wanda give him special glasses to see the Anti-Fairies who are causing the problem.

episodes.name: Super Bike
episodes.overview: For the annual Father-Son bike race, Timmy wishes up a bike that's unstoppable, unbreakable, and totally modern and cool: Super Bike. But the bike gets super jealous of Timmy's friends and hobbies.

episodes.name: A Mile In My Shoes
episodes.overview: Timmy thinks Cosmo and Wanda have it easy being godparents, and vice versa. To prove each other's points, Timmy becomes a fairy and Cosmo and Wanda become normal kids. But Timmy can't control his magic and has to undergo training from Jorgen von Strangle, and Cosmo and Wanda have a tough time dealing with Timmy's parents and school.

episodes.name: Foul Balled
episodes.overview: When Timmy asks his fairies to use their magic to make Chester the “best baseball player” ever, things go from bad, to great, to worse.

episodes.name: The Boy Who Would Be Queen
episodes.overview: Timmy tells Trixie Tang that he has a great gift for her, so he can be invited to her party. Obviously, he's lying. Later that day, Timmy and Cosmo start making of girls, and Wanda becomes so angry she turns Timmy into a girl. Timmy decides being a girl can help him/her figure out what Trixie would like for her birthday, so he/she goes off to the mall...but not without revenge on his godparents for turning him into a girl...he wishes Cosmo was a woman and Wanda was a man.

episodes.name: Totally Spaced Out
episodes.overview: Timmy goes to an amusement park in Friday the 13th and he figures that something is destroying the park, until Cosmo and Wanda give him special glasses to see the Anti-Fairies who are causing the problem.

episodes.name: The Switch Glitch
episodes.overview: Timmy is angry with Vicky, as the babysitter always gets her way, so he wishes he could be her babysitter so he can get revenge. He eventually grows guilty, and things get worse when Cosmo and Wanda get reassigned to Vicky!

episodes.name: Mighty Mom and Dyno Dad
episodes.overview: Timmy, sick of his parents rushing to work and coming home late, tired, and never having any time for him, wishes that they had superpowers.

episodes.name: Knighty Knight
episodes.overview: After being ripped off by the Camelot Fair, Timmy wishes he was in the real Camelot, but Timmy's parents somehow come along with him and are about to be eaten by a dragon!

episodes.name: Fairy Fairy Quite Contrary
episodes.overview: Timmy becomes suspicious of a rich boy named Remy when he notices that he can be better than him in many situations. Timmy eventually learns that he has a fairy godparent.

guest_stars.character: Remy Buxaplenty / Phone Voice / Dale Dimmadome (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: Nectar of The Odds
episodes.overview: Timmy needs to raise money for tickets to see Crash Nebula on Ice, so he starts a lemonade stand. But his lemonade tastes terrible! That's when Cosmo, stupidly, puts his sweaty socks into a glass. Believe it or not, it makes the lemonade taste a lot better. But it also starts granting everyone's wishes!

episodes.name: Hail to the Chief
episodes.overview: Timmy decides to run for Student Body President to capture the attention and affection of the lovely, popular Trixie Tang.

episodes.name: Twistory
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes the great American leaders into his treehouse talk show to finish his report, but because they have vanished from history, the United States reverts to being a British colony and Timmy must find a way to get them back.

episodes.name: Fool's Day Out
episodes.overview: Timmy is pranked by his parents and fairies on Fourth of July. In retaliation, Timmy summons the April Fool, who does very dangerous pranks.

episodes.name: Deja Vu
episodes.overview: Timmy is always stressed out at the end of the day, with being beat up by Francis, failing grades, and Vicky!  So he decides to have a reset watch so he can turn back time and redo things. But when Vicky gets hold of the watch, who only knows what will happen next!

episodes.name: Scary Godparents
episodes.overview: During his worst Halloween ever, Timmy wishes that everyone's Halloween costumes were real and scary.

episodes.name: Ruled Out
episodes.overview: Tired of having strict parents, Timmy wishes for care-free parents.

episodes.name: That's Life
episodes.overview: Timmy's mother is desperately trying to win the annual Dimmsdale Veg-Out, but her garden looks more like a barren desert. To help his mom, Timmy wishes that her garden was "full of life."

episodes.name: Shiny Teeth
episodes.overview: An evil Dentist steals teen pop singer Chip Skylark's teeth and only one person can stop him: The Tooth Fairy.

episodes.name: Odd Odd West
episodes.overview: Timmy travels back in time to the Old West to find the lost deed for Dimmsdale Flats.

episodes.name: Cosmo Con
episodes.overview: Cosmo is chosen to hold the notoriously short Fairy Convention. But things go haywire when he decides to hold it in Timmy's bathroom, especially while they're having Mr. Crocker over for dinner!

episodes.name: Wanda's Day Off
episodes.overview: Wanda's been working so hard, the boys give her a day off. Cosmo promises not to grant any wishes, to keep chaos at a minimum. But when Timmy has trouble doing his animal report, Cosmo messes things up big time!

episodes.name: Information Stupor Highway
episodes.overview: Timmy is writing a e-mail to Trixie, about the school dance, but Timmy's parents come in and make the e-mail all about love, and they send it! So Timmy transforms into computer data to try to retrieve the letter before it reaches Trixie.

episodes.name: Odd Jobs
episodes.overview: Cosmo and Wanda create a magical website that gives Mr. Turner new jobs.

episodes.name: Movie Magic
episodes.overview: Timmy wants to impress Trixie Tang with a film, but Tad and Chad have produced their own big-budget film starring actual actors. Although Timmy knows he can't use his fairies to win the competition, there is nothing against Da Rules that says he can't film actual historical events as part of his movie.

episodes.name: Love Struck!
episodes.overview: Timmy learns from Cupid that Tootie is destined to be his special someone, but he doesn't want to waste his first kiss on Vicky's little sister instead of Trixie, so he creates an elaborate Valentine for Trixie consisting of dancers and a song. After Trixie rejects him yet again, Timmy decides to wish all girls to another part of the world before Tootie can get to him.

episodes.name: Most Wanted Wish
episodes.overview: After every wimpy kid in the school was picked over him by Tad and Chad, and Trixie chose a rock over him as her lab partner, Timmy wishes that he was the most wanted kid on Earth.

episodes.name: This is Your Wish
episodes.overview: Cosmo's overbearing mother, Mama Cosma, makes another attempt at prying him away from Wanda and Timmy by luring them onto a game show called "This is Your Wish" hosted by Billy Crystal Ball.

episodes.name: Engine Blocked
episodes.overview: Mr. Turner is going through mid-life crisis and impulsively buys a sports car from Vicky. Timmy wishes that he was car so he could spend time with his dad.

episodes.name: The Crimson Chin Meets Mighty Mom and Dyno Dad!
episodes.overview: Timmy accidentally wishes Nega-Chin out of a comic book and allows Cosmo and Wanda to grant his wishes.

episodes.name: Sleepover And Over
episodes.overview: Timmy's friends, A.J. and Chester argue and break their friendship. When they each invite him to their respective sleepovers on the same night, to watch a Crash Nebula/Crimson Chin crossover special, this creates a problem for Timmy. How will he join both of them without being discovered? How will he reunite his friends?

episodes.name: Mother Nature
episodes.overview: Mrs. Turner wins a contest that makes her the new weather-person of the local news, and Timmy wishes that everything she will predict would come true.

episodes.name: Beddy Bye
episodes.overview: Being annoyed by his inability to stay up all night and thus missing night-time events, Timmy wishes for the world to have no sleep at all. He soon realizes that everyone needs sleep to function.

guest_stars.character: Chuck Cheeseley / Human Pin-Cushion / Crocodile Man (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: The Grass Is Always Greener
episodes.overview: After overhearing an out of context conversation by his parents where they'd wish that they were more like Mr. Dinkleberg and without any children, Timmy gets upset and decides to fulfill their wish by running away from home.

episodes.name: The Secret Origin of Denzel Crocker
episodes.overview: March 15 is the day that every child fears - the day where Mr. Crocker is at his meanest, and the reason of his extreme unhappiness remain a mystery, so Timmy uses the Time Scooter to go back to Crocker's childhood to solve it. Timmy finds a shocking secret that involves Crocker and fairies.

episodes.name: So Totally Spaced Out
episodes.overview: After cute and cuddly creatures named "Gigglepies" invade and capture Yugopotamia, Mark Prince flees his planet to enlist the help of the "mighty Earth warrior" Timmy Turner in defeating the threat.

episodes.name: MicroPhony
episodes.overview: It's summer time and all the parents are leaving their children under Vicky's slave care, so Timmy decides to use his treehouse as a radio station to broadcast a message to all the parents in Dimmsdale: To spend time with their kids in the summer.

episodes.name: The Big Scoop!
episodes.overview: Chester and A.J. decide to dig up some dirt on their friend, who has inexplicably joined the popular clique after a sudden disappearance of his parents.

episodes.name: Pipe Down!
episodes.overview: After failing to complete his block version of the Eiffel Tower and after getting yelled at several times, Timmy wishes that everything was completely silent, but problems arise when a meteor is heading for Earth and Timmy can't wish it gone!!!! Will Timmy save all sound?

episodes.name: Crime Wave
episodes.overview: Timmy wants to get a new Crimson Chin comic while bathing, so he wishes himself there, but appears in the nude and must run all the way back home naked. Meanwhile, inside the comic book Timmy left behind, the Crimson Chin fights H20lga!

episodes.name: Odd Ball
episodes.overview: After Timmy's V-Cube burns out due to him selfishly overplaying it, his parents refuse to buy him a new one and Timmy is forced to get a job by playing on the local basketball team, the Dimmsdale Ballhogs.

episodes.name: Where's Wanda?
episodes.overview: After Timmy wins a student motion picture fair at his school in a stunning upset with his goldfish costumed as Jaws, Wanda mysteriously disappears after a brief power outage, and it's up to Timmy and Cosmo to solve the mystery.

episodes.name: Imaginary Gary
episodes.overview: After his parents ignore him yet again, Timmy remembers his imaginary friend he made up in his youth, Gary, and decides to wish him real.

episodes.name: Miss Dimmsdale
episodes.overview: Timmy tries to keep Vicky from cheating in the Miss Dimmsdale beatuy contest.

episodes.name: Mind Over Magic
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that he could read minds.

episodes.name: Kung Timmy
episodes.overview: Francis beats up Timmy again, and after Mr. Turner tries to intervene, he gets beaten up too, resulting in the bully taking the Turner's own house and car. After briefly training in kung-fu, Timmy decides fight Francis.

episodes.name: Which Witch Is Which?
episodes.overview: Who really founded Dimmsdale? Timmy goes back in time to Colonial Dimmsdale to meet the legendary Dale Dimm, and almost gets burned at the stake in the process.

episodes.name: Hard Copy
episodes.overview: While Wanda takes a terrifed Cosmo to the doctor, she leaves Timmy with a magic photo copier that can make copies of anything. He then makes a life-size Darth Vader action figure that tries to destroy Dimmsdale.

episodes.name: Parent Hoods
episodes.overview: Timmy's parents are mistaken for wanted outlaws, and Timmy tries to catch the real crooks.

episodes.name: Chip Off the Old Chip
episodes.overview: To win the lead role in the school musical with Trixie Tang, Timmy wishes that he had Chip Skylark's voice.

episodes.name: Snow Bound
episodes.overview: Timmy's dad thinks mom is in danger from an abominable snowman so he rushes up to mount Dimmsdale...

episodes.name: The Big Superhero Wish
episodes.overview: In another case of ""Be careful what you wish for,"" Timmy wishes the world was more like a Crimson Chin comic book, and Cosmo and Wanda turn him and all his friends into superheroes!

episodes.name: Vicky Loses Her Icky
episodes.overview: Have you ever wondered what makes Vicky so mean? The answer is surprisingly easy: She has a bug up her butt.When timmy wishes that his mean and nasty babysitter   would be nice, a magical bug containing Vicky's evil essence crawls crawls from out of her butt leaving behind a sweet and docile teenager. Vicky is now a total saint. But the evil   Has to go somewhere, which means that   the bug is on the hunt for its next host.

episodes.name: Pixies Inc.
episodes.overview: Pixies have bought fairy world! Under the new management of the monotonous and very corporate Pixies, everyone's wishes are being denied. So Timmy challenges the head pixie to a winner-takes-all game of miniature golf:   If Timmy wins, the pixies will leave fairy world, but if he loses, Cosmo and Wanda will have to leave Timmy forever.

episodes.name: Baby Face
episodes.overview: Now that Timmy's old enough, he doesn't have to be subjected to all the kiddie stuff at Flappy Bob's Happy Learnatorium anymore.

episodes.name: Mr. Right
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that everything he said was right, and he gets exactly what he asked for.

episodes.name: Power Pals
episodes.overview: Timmy decides to wish for a group of superheroes to be his new friends

guest_stars.character: Elmer / Sanjay / Nerd / Shark #2 / Angry Tourist (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: Emotion Commotion
episodes.overview: After being embarrassed in public, Timmy wishes he has no emotions and ends up working for the CIA.

episodes.name: Lights... Camera... Adam!
episodes.overview: Timmy is an stunt-boy in the Crimson Chin movie where he uncovers a plot to discredit the Chin.

episodes.name: A Bad Case of Diary-Uh
episodes.overview: Timmy gets a hold of Vicky's diary and uses her deepest secrets to try to get revenge against her.

guest_stars.character: Bronze Kneecap / P.A. / Dorky Kid / Clown (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: Odd Couple
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for a perfect match for Vicky, and soon Ricky and Vicky fall in love with each other.

episodes.name: Class Clown
episodes.overview: Timmy tries to win the heart of his one true love by wishing that he was the funniest guy on Earth.

episodes.name: Who's Your Daddy?
episodes.overview: It's time for the Father-Son Squirrely Scout competition, but Dad gets called away for work, leaving Timmy without a partner.

episodes.name: Homewrecker
episodes.overview: Timmy is sick of Vicky messing up his house then blaming it on him, so Timmy gets his revenge on Vicky by doing the same.

episodes.name: Crash Nebula
episodes.overview: Sprig Speevak is leaving his parent's farm for an intergalactic academy where he will learn to be a space hero. But first, he has to learn to survive space high school.

episodes.name: Shelf Life
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that Tom Sawyer could come out of his book and help him with his book report.

episodes.name: Fairy Friends and Neighbors
episodes.overview: When Jimmy wishes for friends to hang out with his folks, Cosmo and Wanda are the ones who get stuck with the job.

episodes.name: Just The Two of Us
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that he and Trixie were the only people on the planet.

episodes.name: New Squid in Town
episodes.overview: Mark Chang is on the run from his enraged bride-to-be whom he left at the altar. He looks to the only Earthling who can help, Timmy Turner.

episodes.name: Wish Fixers
episodes.overview: Timmy is ordered to undergo a program that will teach him to make harmless wishes.

episodes.name: Genie Meanie Minie Moe
episodes.overview: Timmy accidentally releases a genie from a magic lava lamp.

episodes.name: Teeth for Two
episodes.overview: Jorgen has to stay with Cosmo and Wanda after the Tooth Fairy thinks he was doing her job (He was actually attempting to remove Timmy's teeth- allegedly the 'dental equivalent of the Hope Diamond'- to use as an engagement ring for her).

episodes.name: Nega-Timmy
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes to do the opposite of what his parents tell him to, and when they say be good, he turns evil.

episodes.name: Love at First Height
episodes.overview: Timmy becomes 16 to ride a rollercoaster and Vicky accidentally falls in love with him and everybody want's to be with Timmy believing that he's a Norwegian super model.

episodes.name: Truth or Cosmoquences
episodes.overview: Cosmo and Wanda receive invitations to their high school reunion.

guest_stars.character: Bucky McBadbat / Monster Emergency Response Man (voice)
guest_stars.name: Rob Paulsen

episodes.name: Beach Bummed
episodes.overview: After some ritual beach-themed bullying, courtesy of Francis, Timmy wishes that he was the strongest guy on the beach.

episodes.name: Just Desserts
episodes.overview: Timmy's wish for a world of desserts could mean an early end for everyone.

episodes.name: You Doo!
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for a You-Doo doll of Francis for revenge. Later on, Timmy gets You-Doo dolls of mostly every main character on the show. Tootie gets the You-Doo of Timmy, and the trouble starts!

episodes.name: Catman Meets The Crimson Chin
episodes.overview: Tired of having sand kicked in his face by Frances, Timmy wishes he was the strongest guy on the beach. But when a whale washes up on shore Timmy grows into a super-sized-hulking-human who quickly becomes the main target of a dangerously armed and heavily funded Seaweed Monster Response Team.

episodes.name: Back To Norm
episodes.overview: Mr. Crocker receives the magic lava lamp as a present and tries to capture Timmy's fairies in a Roadrunner-like manner

episodes.name: The Masked Magician
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes every meal was dessert, but his wish makes the entire town fat.

episodes.name: The Big Bash
episodes.overview: Timmy and Remy get in a hunt, and the winner gets a few rule-free wishes. If Remy wins, Timmy will lose his godparents, and Wandisimo gets Wanda.

episodes.name: Blondas Have More Fun
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for a You-Doo doll of Francis for revenge. Later on, Timmy gets You-Doo dolls of mostly every main character on the show. Tootie gets the You-Doo of Timmy, and the trouble starts!

guest_stars.character: Dr. Poof / Reporter #2 / Kid #2 / Elmer / Binky (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: Five Days Of Flarg
episodes.overview: Mark the alien is missing Flarg on his planet so he has it on Earth.

episodes.name: Go Young, West Man
episodes.overview: Catman fights Crimson Chin Villains in an attempt to find acceptance

guest_stars.character: Truant Officer Shallowgrave / Clown / Birthday Attendee (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: Birthday Wish
episodes.overview: Timmy loans his godparents to Tootie on her birthday to make up for a lousy one.

episodes.name: Timmy's 2-D House of Horror
episodes.overview: Timmy turns a boring 3-D movie volcano into a real volcano but it destroys Vicky's house and her and her family have to live with Timmy, now he must drive them out.

episodes.name: It's A Wishful Life
episodes.overview: Jorgen has to stay with Cosmo and Wanda after the Tooth Fairy thinks he was doing her job (He was actually attempting to remove Timmy's teeth- allegedly the 'dental equivalent of the Hope Diamond'- to use as an engagement ring for her).

episodes.name: Escape From Unwish Island
episodes.overview: Wanda and here sister, Blanda argue about who's life is worse. To see who's is worse they switch bodies and experience life in the other's body.

episodes.name: The Grand Plan
episodes.overview: Cosmo's Fagiggligland (what fairies use to transform into diffrent things) isn't working and might loose his job being Timmy's godparent. The gang must get Anti-Cosmo out of Anti-fairy jail in order to do a transplant performed by Dr. Rip Studwell. But Jorgen Vonstrangle won't let them through or let Anti-Cosmo out!

episodes.name: Hassle in the Castle
episodes.overview: Timmy snoops inside his fairies fishbowl castle, but causes trouble after accidentally wishing back past godkids in the Hall of Infamy.

episodes.name: Remy Rides Again
episodes.overview: Mark the alien is missing Flarg on his planet so he has it on Earth.

episodes.name: Talkin' Trash
episodes.overview: Wanda's father and Timmy must clean up magical garbage in Timmy's house.

episodes.name: Timmy TV
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes Adam west could be a kid again, because he never had a childhood.

episodes.name: Mooooving Day
episodes.overview: Timmy turns a boring 3-D movie volcano into a real volcano but it destroys Vicky's house and her and her family have to live with Timmy, now he must drive them out.

episodes.name: Big Wanda
episodes.overview: Someone’s kidnapped Big Daddy! With the big mob boss missing, Wanda is called in to run the family business. Her first task: a mafia makeover complete with pink trash removal uniforms, pink garbage trucks, and doilies on all the fairy world trash cans.

episodes.name: Oh, Brother
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes he was never born and Jorgen shows how people's lives are better without him.

episodes.name: What's the Difference?
episodes.overview: Timmy's reading a find-it book when Mark Chang, in his traditional alien form, shows up. His changer is broken, and without it, Mandie will find him. In a last ditch effort to save Mark, Timmy wishes the school was like his book. But she is about to turn the school into a crater if Mark doesn’t show himself. If Cosmo and Wanda had their wands, Timmy could just wish her away. But where are the wands hiding?

episodes.name: Smart Attack
episodes.overview: Dad keeps trying to help Timmy with his homework. But he’s not the brightest dad, so any help he gives does more harm than good. How can Timmy get his dad to stop helping without hurting his feelings? He doesn’t. He completely avoids the subject by wishing that his dad was smart. Now that Dad has the brains of a genius, he home-school’s Timmy and pays a lot more attention to things like Timmy’s goldfish. In all the years that Timmy has had his pet fish, not once has he fed them. Dad concludes that they must be a new breed and sets out to dissect the fish in front of the entire scientific community.

episodes.name: Operation FUN
episodes.overview: Remy Buxaplenty has come home from military school for spring break. All he can talk about is how great his new school is, making Timmy, Chester, and AJ very jealous in the process. Timmy decides they should all get to go to Remy’s fancy academy and wishes for three scholarships. Once the boys get to their new school, they find that it is not quite the paradise Remy described -- it’s the exact opposite. The students have to get up before dawn every morning, all the teachers are drill sergeants, and pets are strictly forbidden which means that Timmy’s pet goldfish (a.k.a. Cosmo and Wanda) are confiscated and placed in storage. This of course was Remy’s plan all along, and now that Timmy can’t get to his God Parents, he cannot wish himself out of this nightmare.

episodes.name: Something's Fishy
episodes.overview: Cosmo's Fagiggligland (what fairies use to transform into diffrent things) isn't working and might loose his job being Timmy's godparent. The gang must get Anti-Cosmo out of Anti-fairy jail in order to do a transplant performed by Dr. Rip Studwell. But Jorgen Vonstrangle won't let them through or let Anti-Cosmo out!

episodes.name: Presto Change-O
episodes.overview: Timmy hasn’t studied for a test in Mr. Crocker’s class, so he wishes for a magical device that allows him to change places with anyone who comes in contact with it. Cosmo and Wanda are in a hurry, so they give Timmy his wish. At school, he uses this device to change places with AJ, but after that, his plan backfires. Will Timmy be able to stop Crocker from finding out about Timmy's fairies? Find out.

episodes.name: The Good Ol' Days
episodes.overview: Timmy snoops inside his fairies fishbowl castle, but causes trouble after accidentally wishing back past godkids in the Hall of Infamy.

episodes.name: Future Lost
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for his society to be more futuristic, like a fictional character from one of Dad's old books. However, this society is filled with robots, who are seemingly harmless, but in reality, are evil. Will Timmy escape from this dreaded society?

episodes.name: Timmy The Barbarian
episodes.overview: Remy returns and has a diabolical plan to get Timmy to become his friend and spend more time with him, just so he could get rid of his godparents.

episodes.name: No Substitute for Crazy
episodes.overview: Crocker has fallen into a well and so Timmy's class has been assigned a substitute teacher called Mrs. Sunshine and she seems very-very nice until Timmy wishes for her to be his permanent teacher, she turns out to be even worse than Mr. Crocker when she is really an expert fairy hunter named Mrs. Doombringer.

episodes.name: Mission Responsible
episodes.overview: Timmy offers to baby-sit Poof for Cosmo and Wanda so they can have the night out.

episodes.name: Hairicane
episodes.overview: Sick and tired of his father's bad haircuts, Timmy wishes for indestructible hair with a personality that can't be cut. It then comes to life as it grows and almost destroys Dimmsdale. Meanwhile, Wanda takes Poof to the baby fairy barber shop for his first haircut.

episodes.name: Open Wide And Say Aaagh!
episodes.overview: Timmy has to spend time at the hospital with Vicky as his candy striper nurse.

episodes.name: Odd Pirates
episodes.overview: The Pirates opening game is today, and everyone except Timmy is going. Timmy wishes he was at the game, but when Wanda lets Poof make the wish, they end up on a real Pirate ship. The wands get stolen, they get trapped in a net, and almost get attacked by crocodiles. When Timmy opens his big mouth, the pirate ship becomes land-born. The pirates attack the Pirates games, and the Pirates baseball team helps defeat them.

episodes.name: The Odd Squad
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes Cosmo was a talking car so that he and his fairies can search for the missing Mama Cosma.

episodes.name: For Emergencies Only
episodes.overview: Feeling that Cosmo and Wanda are neglecting him for Poof, Timmy gets his godparents to give him his own magic wand with ten wishes on it.

episodes.name: Cheese & Crockers
episodes.overview: On Happy Half Day where "half-ness" is celebrated, Timmy wishes for a machine that lets him become half-Timmy/ half-whatever, but it also turns Mr. Crocker into a cheese powered megalomaniac.

episodes.name: The Land Before Timmy
episodes.overview: Sick of technology ruining his life, Timmy wishes to live in a simpler time. He and all of Dimmsdale are then sent to the Stone Age.

episodes.name: King Chang
episodes.overview: Mark Chang is called back to the planet Yugopotamia to become King when Princess Mandie sizes the throne from his father, and Timmy has to get help from Vicky to save Mark and his people.

episodes.name: The End of the Universe-ity
episodes.overview: Dark Laser's back and after trying (and failing) to destroy Timmy, he adopts the saying, "if you can't beat 'em, get 'em to join you." He offers Timmy a scholarship to "Dark-Mouth University" in an effort to get him to become his evil apprentice. Timmy refuses but Mom and Dad – excited that someone else is going to pay for Timmy's college – eagerly accept the offer. Timmy is given a dark suit with dark powers and the proviso that if Timmy tries it and doesn't want it, Dark Laser will leave Earth alone forever. Timmy agrees, and soon it seems he's fallen under the evil spell of the evil suit.

episodes.name: Sooper Poof
episodes.overview: Poof is trying to get the hang of shape shifting but unfortunately he takes after Cosmo! And worse, one of his attempts has him crash landing in front of the Turner house, where Mom and Dad find him and become convinced he's an alien super baby they need to raise to fight for truth and justice! But Timmy can't just steal Poof back because Mom and Dad have fallen in love with the little guy, so he must devise another way of getting Poof back to Cosmo and Wanda before Dad's attempts to turn the baby into a super hero get them all in trouble!

episodes.name: Wishing Well
episodes.overview: Timmy's been running Cosmo and Wanda ragged so Jorgen takes him to "Wishing Well", a state of the art rehabilitation facility where he can learn to wish less and be more independent. He meets two other kids with fairies and together they battle their darkest fears, escape from precarious situations…and make breakfast, all without wishing. In the end, they learn independence only when they band together to escape, which they do without any fairy assistance whatsoever. But escaping wasn't part of Jorgen's plan…or was it? Either way, it worked!

episodes.name: Wishy Washy
episodes.overview: Timmy's wish for a magical car wash that rejuvenates anything that goes through it so his father can restore his beloved Striker Z sports car, but fossils of dinosuars and cavemen also go through it causing them to come back to life and run amok in Dimmsdale, as do Cosmo and Wanda, turning them into rebellious teenagers.

episodes.name: Poof's Playdate
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for some fairy babies to play with lonely Poof, turning Cosmo, Wanda, Jorgen, the Tooth Fairy, Juandisimo, and Cupid into fairy babies.

episodes.name: Vicky Gets Fired
episodes.overview: Despite all the ways Vicky has tortured Timmy, it's only when she accidentally erases a videotape that Mom and Dad actually fire her. Determined to get a job, Vicky decides she wants to be mayor and takes over the city. As she's ready to make Vickyville a whole new country, Timmy, who's happy for the first time, realizes he's got to get Vicky out of office and back as his babysitter in order to maintain peace.

episodes.name: Chinred Spirits
episodes.overview: Timmy's disappointed to see how boring the Crimson Chin comics have become lately. When he spends a day with the Chin, he sees why - the Chin is lonely. Timmy wishes up a super girlfriend for him, except now the comic is both boring and romantic, yuck! Desperate, Timmy unknowingly makes a wish that changes everything, so he must undo his wish - and fast.

episodes.name: 9 Lives
episodes.overview: Binky is ill so Jorgen comes to cheer him up by telling him a magical story about Timmy Cosmo and Wanda, but this is bad news for the trio as what ever Jorgen says will happen in the story. This will be tricky for the two heroes and pack mule.

episodes.name: Dread & Breakfast
episodes.overview: Dad's quit his job to make sock monkeys, and there's no income for the Turners...until Mom turns the house into a bed and breakfast. That'd be fine, if the first guests weren't Mr. Crocker, Dark Laser and Tootie who either want to destroy Timmy or kiss him. As Timmy runs around frantically trying to stay one step ahead of his house guests, he must find a way to get everyone out without using the very fairy magic Crocker is hoping to catch him using.

episodes.name: Bad Heir Day
episodes.overview: Crocker gets a hold of Poof and decides to groom him to be the heir to his "fame and fortune."

episodes.name: Freaks and Greeks
episodes.overview: When Timmy's parents go to a toga party, his fairies take him to one on Mount Olympus where he accidentily destroys it with a thunderbolt, so the gods move the party to his house.

episodes.name: Mice-Capades
episodes.overview: When Poof watches too much of the violent classic "cat and mouse" cartoon, "Cheesy and Sleazy", he turns Timmy and Vicky into the characters from the show.

episodes.name: Formula For Disaster
episodes.overview: Poof's refusal to take his medicine and Crocker's visit to the Turner residence to complain about Timmy's bad grades leads to chaos in the Turner household.

episodes.name: Birthday Bashed
episodes.overview: Timmy looks forward to his birthday until Jorgen reminds him that each birthday draws him a year closer to losing his fairies; however, Timmy isn't worried because his folks always forget his birthday, but he then panics when they seem to remember it this time.

episodes.name: Momnipresent
episodes.overview: Timmy's preperations for the party of the year are interrupted by his mother who wants to spend some quality time with him. He then sneaks away every chance he gets to get the party ready.

episodes.name: Anti-Poof
episodes.overview: When Poof's anti-fairy counterpart, Foop, is born, it is up to Poof to save his loved ones and Fairy World from him.

episodes.name: Squirrely Puffs
episodes.overview: It's a race between the Squirrely Scouts and the Cream Puffs to the top of Mount Doom. Will Timmy's team survive this harrowing challenge, or will Mom and the "girls" make them turn tail?

episodes.name: Add-a-Dad
episodes.overview: Timmy's dad is very busy working, so busy in fact, that when Timmy & him are doing something fun, he suddenly has to leave & Timmy's left alone. So he finds a solution, to wish up many dads, so that every time one of them has to leave, he has another one, but then there's too many dads! And they all want Timmy! Then when he realizes he doesn't want or need many dads, he has to find a way to get rid of them.......by sending them to another planet and gives them Timmy plushies so they can be happy!

episodes.name: Fly Boy
episodes.overview: Everybody in Dimmsdale is watching the latest horror film, "Fly Boy". But Timmy isn't allowed to, so when he wishes to become a "fly on the wall" in order to see it, the real horror begins.

episodes.name: Temporary Fairy
episodes.overview: Jorgen serves as over-adventurious Timmy's temproary godparent when Cosmo and Wanda become too busy with Poof.

episodes.name: Crocker Shocker
episodes.overview: Fairy World's magic is shut down when Mr. Crocker is hypnotized into no longer believing in fairies.

episodes.name: Super Zero
episodes.overview: When Cosmo gets ousted from the house for being too annoying, he then becomes Dimmdale's newest superhero.

episodes.name: Dadracadabra
episodes.overview: Mr. Crocker suspects that Timmy's Dad is a fairy when Timmy and his fairies help him with his magic

episodes.name: Timmy Turnip
episodes.overview: Timmy meets his grandparents and quickly wishes they never came to America. He finds himself back in Ustinkistan, his grandparents' native country, and he must somehow get on the next boat home.

episodes.name: One Man Banned
episodes.overview: After Timmy is rejected from the school band, he wishes everyone would love his music. But when Timmy gets his first taste of acclaim, Wanda has to stop him before he becomes completely fame-crazy.

episodes.name: Frenemy Mine
episodes.overview: Vicky becomes Timmy's friend after he saves her life.

episodes.name: Double Oh Schnozmo
episodes.overview: Cosmo's brother, Schnozmo, comes to visit, claiming to be a secret agent But when he turns out to be nothing but a con man, Wanda makes him take part in a real spy adventure to spare Cosmo's feelings.

episodes.name: Planet Poof
episodes.overview: Feeling ignored by his family,Poof runs away to Yugopotamia where the unappreciated Queen uses his cuteness to scare the residents into giving her whatever she wants.

episodes.name: The Boss Of Me
episodes.overview: When Timmy goes to visit his father's office, he wishes up a pencil that will last forever. This impresses Dad's boss so much that he hires Timmy and orders him to fire Dad.

episodes.name: He Poofs, He Scores
episodes.overview: Timmy tries out for the soccer team his father coaches, the Victims. He accidently swallows Poof, however, who goes right to his brain and makes him the greatest soccer player ever.

episodes.name: Play Date of Doom
episodes.overview: Foop escapes from prison seeking revenge on Poof.

episodes.name: Teacher's Pet
episodes.overview: When Timmy wishes that he was the teacher's pet, Poof turns him into Mr. Crocker's guinea pig.

episodes.name: Chicken Poofs
episodes.overview: Poof has the contageous Chicken Poofs disease that turns him into a chicken, and everyone he sneazes on turns into chickens as well. He then flees from the hospital, and Timmy and Cosmo try to catch him before he infects all of Dimmsdale while Wanda and Dr. Rip Studwell search for a cure.

episodes.name: Stupid Cupid
episodes.overview: Timmy seeks help from Cupid to win the love of Trixie Tang, but Cupid is on vacation. So Timmy has Cosmo fill in for the love god, but Cosmo only causes himself, Wanda, Mr. and Mrs. Turner, and Mr. Crocker to fall head over heals in love with all sorts of things.

episodes.name: Manic Mom Day
episodes.overview: When Timmy envies his mother's life, Wanda makes makes them swap bodies for a day on a bet that if Timmy finds a mother's life easier, Wanda will have to spend a week as a chicken; otherwise, Timmy will have to go a week without magic.

episodes.name: Crocker of Gold
episodes.overview: Crocker captures Cosmo, mistaking him for a leperchaun, and Cosmo then steals a pot of gold from a clan of real leperchauns to buy his freedom. The clan then holds Wanda and Poof hostage until Cosmo and Timmy replace it.

episodes.name: Love Triangle
episodes.overview: Poof is upset his parents want him to take the lead role in the school play, but he quickly changes his mind after his new crush, Goldie Goldenglow gets the female lead role, but to get the role, he has to beat his archnemesis Foop, who also fell for Goldie.[2]

episodes.name: Spellementery School
episodes.overview: With Poof's first day in Spellementary School, he and Foop compete to be the most popular student there, but Foop takes it to extremes when his classmates don't accept him, and its up to Poof to stop his anti-fairy counterpart from tearing apart the school!

episodes.name: Operation Dinkelberg
episodes.overview: Timmy's Dad becomes obsessed with proving his neighbor, Mr. Dinkleberg is evil. He enlists Timmy to help him spy on Dinkleberg by dressing up like a girl scout!

episodes.name: Invasion of the Dads
episodes.overview: Timmy's previous wish for a Planet of the Dads backfires when the Dads realize the one thing missing from their lives is Mom, and they come to steal her away from Dad and Timmy! It's up to Timmy, Cosmo (in a magnify glass disguise), Wanda (in ice cube disguise, who was forced to remain in a freezer to prevent from melting), Poof (in a bee disguise), Mark Chang and a rather bumbling "Real Dad" to thwart the Dads and rescue Mom!

episodes.name: Take and Fake
episodes.overview: Timmy borrows Mark Chang's fake-a-fier in order to attend Trixie's costume party.

episodes.name: Cosmo Rules
episodes.overview: When Jorgen von Strangle gets the trick-ups (bouts of fairy hiccups that cause bouts of cheesy magician-like parlor magic) he isn't able to enforce Da Rules, so he must pass it on to his closest available relative until he gets better. Unfortunately, his closest available relative is his long-lost cousin Cosmo as his Nana Boom Boom was playing Explosive Bingo and his cousin Leonard Von Strangle was on a trip in the Bahamas.

episodes.name: Farm Pit
episodes.overview: Mr. Turner has been fired from his job, so he tries to start up a farm instead. Unfortunately, he has no luck at growing anything, so Timmy wishes his father's crops would grow huge. But now Timmy's father has so much success that he wants his family to stay on the farm forever!

episodes.name: Crock Talk
episodes.overview: After mysterious monster appearences of monsters on Dimmsdale, Crocker starts a webshow to comment it, and asks for viewers to call if they see a monster. Unfortunately, Timmy wishes for them, Dad calls Crocker everynight and he gets a freepass to film the fairies.

episodes.name: Food Fight
episodes.overview: Tired of his mom's nasty food, Timmy wishes that his mom was the best cook in the world, but when she enters to a cooking competition, the magic wont work and she has to face the challenge alone.

episodes.name: Please Don't Feed The Turners
episodes.overview: Doug Dimmadome selects the Turners to go on a space mission, but it turns out it was really Dark Laser in disguise with an elaborate plan to take revenge on Timmy and trap the Turners in a space zoo on his Death Ball.

episodes.name: Lights Out
episodes.overview: After Timmy tells Poof a scary story, the baby's' crying keeps him up all night, so Timmy wishes for no light for twelve hours of day. Little does Timmy know, that when his godparents are kept in the dark for longer than eight hours, they become "Scary Fairies" and turn on their godchild.

episodes.name: Dad Overboard
episodes.overview: After Mr. Turner gets lost while looking for their hotel and land on a deserted island, he struggles to make a boat to save his family, and to prove his masculinity he doesn't let anyone help him. Timmy wishes for relaxation items, (hammock,Ipod,Club sandwiches,etc).Meanwhile, Poof finds a nuclear bomb in the sand and Cosmo activates it, putting the Turners' life at risk.

episodes.name: Old Man And The C-
episodes.overview: When Mr. Turner reveals he dropped off school at 5th grade, he attempts to graduate from Dimmsdale Elementary School to make his son proud.

episodes.name: Balance of Flour
episodes.overview: Centuries ago, the Anti-Fairies and Fairies started an annual bake-off to determine which species gets godchildren, this year, Jorgen von Strangle's recipe is at risk, and Anti-Cosmo and Anti-Wanda are determined to make sure they make Timmy their godchild by stealing the recipe and cheating the fairies out of the competition.

episodes.name: Poltergeeks
episodes.overview: Timmy has Cosmo, Wanda, and Poof pose as ghosts so that his parents can re-live their glory days as ghostbusters.

episodes.name: Beach Blanket Bozos
episodes.overview: During a trip to Hawaii, Timmy wishes that his parents were the best surfers ever, but that wish starts a wish limbo, in which they won't stop fighting until only one prevails as best surfer ever in Hawaii.

episodes.name: When Losers Attack
episodes.overview: Timmy Turner’s enemies collaborate to form the League of Super Evil Revenge Seekers (L.O.S.E.R.S.) in order to annihilate him. When the Fairy-clipse, a rare astronomical event that happens every million years, prevents Cosmo and Wanda from using their magic to save him, Timmy is forced to outwit the L.O.S.E.R.S. himself.

episodes.name: Fairly OddPet
episodes.overview: Timmy adopts a mischievous and magical fairy dog named Sparky. However, owning a fairy dog proves to be a much bigger challenge than Timmy could have ever predicted.

episodes.name: Dinklescouts!
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes Mr. Dinkleberg would replace Dad as Squirrely Scout leader.

episodes.name: I Dream of Cosmo
episodes.overview: Cosmo loses his memory and mistakenly thinks he's supposed to grant wishes for Timmy's father.

episodes.name: Turner & Pooch
episodes.overview: Mr. Crocker realizes that Sparky has magical powers. Eager to use the fairy dog’s powers to fulfill his own wishes, Mr. Crocker hypnotizes Sparky in an attempt to turn him against Timmy.

episodes.name: Dumbbell Curve
episodes.overview: Crocker grades on a bell curve so Timmy wishes everyone was dumber than him. Unfortunately, a meteor threatens Earth and Timmy’s the only one smart enough to stop it.

episodes.name: The Terrible Twosome
episodes.overview: Poof is going through the Terrible Twos, and Foop uses this to cause mayhem in Dimmsdale.

episodes.name: App Trap
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for the world's coolest smart phone.

episodes.name: Force of Nature
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes the animals would clean up after themselves.

episodes.name: Viral Vidiots
episodes.overview: Crocker kidnaps Timmy's mom because he thinks she's a troll who possesses magic.

episodes.name: School of Crock
episodes.overview: Mr. Crocker becomes a teacher at the Fairy Academy; Poof begins to learn how to talk.

episodes.name: Cosmonopoly
episodes.overview: Timmy, his father and the fairies get stuck in a board game created by Cosmo.

episodes.name: Hero Hound
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes Sparky would get a chance to be heroic, while Dad thinks he can talk to animals.

episodes.name: A Boy and His Dog-Boy
episodes.overview: After making a deal with Dad, Crocker becomes best friends with Dinkleberg; Timmy wishes for 5,000 Timmys for the Planet of the Dads.

episodes.name: Crock Blocked
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes that Mr. Crocker would disappear, and Mr. Crocker becomes invisible.

episodes.name: The Past and the Furious
episodes.overview: When Cosmo and Wanda bring Timmy back through time to meet their former Godchildren, his interactions with them alter the future.

episodes.name: Let Sleeper Dogs Lie
episodes.overview: Crocker tries to program Sparky as an unwitting sleeper agent in his war against Timmy and the fairies.

episodes.name: Cat-Astrophe
episodes.overview: Catman mistakes Sparky for his old archenemy Dogman.

episodes.name: Jerk of All Trades
episodes.overview: Timmy gets Jorgen fired. He helps Jorgen find a new job.

episodes.name: Snack Attack
episodes.overview: Sparky makes his own magic dog treats. Crocker tries to buy one million of them in order to make a wish

episodes.name: Turning into Turner
episodes.overview: Using Timmy's DNA, Crocker pretends to be Timmy from the future.

episodes.name: The Wand That Got Away
episodes.overview: Cosmo loses his wand and Timmy and the gang must help find it.

episodes.name: Dimmsdale Tales
episodes.overview: When Dad forgets all of the supplies for the Squirrely Scouts camping trip, Timmy tries to smooth things over with scary stories around a campfire.

episodes.name: Love at First Bark
episodes.overview: Sparky is forbidden from dating Dinkleberg's new dog.

episodes.name: Desperate Without Housewives
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes all women away to end Mom's constant nagging.

episodes.name: Stage Fright
episodes.overview: After deciding she wants to be an actress, Vicky forces Timmy to help her get her first role.

episodes.name: Gone Flushin
episodes.overview: Dad flushes Timmy and the fairies down the toilet.

episodes.name: Turner Back Time
episodes.overview: Timmy's ancestors get new careers, which leads to Timmy's family to act like rich spoiled brats.

episodes.name: Weirdos on a Train
episodes.overview: After making a deal with Dad, Crocker becomes best friends with Dinkleberg.

episodes.name: Tons of Timmys
episodes.overview: Timmy wishes for 5,000 Timmys for the Planet of the Dads.

episodes.name: Lame Ducks
episodes.overview: Dad starts a neighborhood watch program.

episodes.name: A Perfect Nightmare
episodes.overview: Timmy tries to win a contest by wishing that he had the perfect family.

episodes.name: Fairly Odd Fairy Tales
episodes.overview: When Poof has trouble falling asleep, Wanda tries to help by reading him a book of classic fairy tales.

episodes.name: One Flu Over the Crocker's Nest
Goldie-Crocks and the Three Fair Bears
